gnat.comparison
Class FloatComparator

java.lang.Object
  gnat.comparison.FloatComparator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Comparator<java.lang.Float>
public class FloatComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<java.lang.Float>

A Comparator for float values. Used e.g. to sort Lists numerically instead of lexically. 

 Hashtable hash = new Hashtable();
 hash.add...
 
 Vector keys = new Vector(hash.keySet());
 FloatComparator fc = new FloatComparator();
 Collections.sort(keys, fc);
 
 for (Enumeration e = keys.elements(); e.hasMoreElements();) {
     Float key = (Float)e.nextElement();
     Object o = hash.get(key);
 }

Method Detail

compare

public int compare(java.lang.Float o1,
                   java.lang.Float o2)
Compares to numerical values and returns either a negative value, zero, or a positive value. Negative return values indicate that the float value of o1 is less than that of o2, zero indicates that both are equal, and positive values indicate that o1 is greater than o2.

In particular, it returns Float.intValue() of o1 - o2.
